# URL Monitor — module agents

Five logical modules share one flat `app/` tree. Each has a scoped rule (auto-attached via globs) and an **@ tag** for explicit handoff.

| Tag | Module | Rule file |
|-----|--------|-----------|
| `@platform` | Bootstrap, settings, DB, errors, health | `platform.mdc` |
| `@monitor-api` | Monitor CRUD & validation | `monitor-api.mdc` |
| `@check-engine` | HTTP probe & UP/DOWN state machine | `check-engine.mdc` |
| `@coordinator` | Background tick loop & due-monitor fan-out | `coordinator.mdc` |
| `@observability` | Check/transition history & status summary | `observability.mdc` |

Full architecture: `ARCHITECTURE.md`.

## Handoff

- Use **@ tags** when the task clearly belongs to one module or when switching context (e.g. “@check-engine add TLS verify option”).
- When a change crosses modules, pick a **lead module** (where most edits land) and list other tags to consult — do not edit another module's files without stating why.
- Shared files (`app/main.py`, `app/routers/monitors.py`): only the owning sections listed in each module rule.

## Cross-cutting (all modules)

- No default values on **function parameters** (see `AGENTS.md`; semgrep hook).
- Config via Pydantic Settings + DI (`pydantic-settings.mdc`).
- Async I/O end-to-end; async tests with `httpx` + `ASGITransport` (`async-consistency.mdc`).
- Routes raise domain exceptions; handlers live in `app/main.py` (`structured-errors.mdc`).

## Test ownership

| Module | Tests |
|--------|-------|
| Platform | `tests/conftest.py`, `tests/test_health.py` |
| Monitor API | `tests/test_api_monitors.py` |
| Check Engine | `tests/test_checker.py` |
| Coordinator | `tests/test_scheduler.py` |
| Observability | `tests/test_api_history.py` |
| Cross-cutting | `tests/test_integration.py` — lead **@platform**, involve others as needed |
